last 3 years, I guess I should be used to the rampant pessimism of the majority of the EQ player-base.  Unfortunately, used to it or not, I find it to be my single worst pet-peeve about this game.<br>
<br>
For whatever reason, it seems that NO CLASS in EQ ever has anything positive to say about their class.  Don't believe me? Read message boards for shamans, clerics, druids (the pinnacle of class-whining), and necromancers.  (I use these classes to illustrate the point, because I've spent time on the boards of these classes and know how much they whine, however I'd bet money you'll see this kind of whining to some degree on every class board.)  In fact, if you believe what you read on these boards as a whole, every class in the game is broken beyond repair and no one, even the &quot;holy trinity&quot; classes can get groups.<br>
<br>
Overall, I say that's a load of BS, but I have some advice for you:  IT'S A GAME, IF YOU AREN'T HAVING FUN, DON'T PLAY!<br>
<br>
Now admittedly there are valid class issues that need to be addressed.  Many of them to be frank.  However, whining, complaining, bitching and moaning about how your class is broken, serves NO PURPOSE.  And to be honest, if you think SOE is going to respond to threats, read Furor's posts over on the Fires of Heaven website and see how that turned out.  You can't threaten SOE and intimidation is going to go no where fast.  However, there is a solution:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I agree with being united. I agree with presenting ideas and issues to Sony about wizards. But Sony isn't going to respond to threats. Yes, Absor reads message boards. But he only responds to those that he feels are intelligent conversations.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This is one of the single, clearest gems of wisdom ever put forth on the subject of class balance, and I applaud the one who wrote it.  Open, or attempt to open, a reasonable dialog with Sony, and you might be surprised how it works out.  Druids did exactly this sort of thing and got a lot of class issues fixed, lending them the appearance of a &quot;most favored class&quot; to the bulk of the other classes.  Chances are good that if there is a valid issue and we present our case clearly and with suggested fixes it'll get a lot more consideration than organized walk-outs or being bitter.<br>
<br>
Also keep in mind the big picture.  No class exists in a vacuum and one seemingly minor change here can have ripples that make problems elsewhere.  Sometimes, no matter how broken something may be, fixing it creates 10x worse problems then just leaving it alone.<br>
<br>
Overall though, I'd have to say wizards are no more, or less, broken than any other class I've ever played. (And if you call be &quot;uber&quot; you obviously don't know me, my highest level toon isn't even 57th level yet.) <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=614716">Thyrbit Firefrog</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elasto>Elasto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1360<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/12/03 8:26 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards of Norrath UNITE!</span><hr size=1> You're absolutely right.<br>
<br>
I know people who are deeply depressed with the state of their cleric, chanter, rogue, druid, wiz etc. Some become very vocal and very bitter. Yet there are many others who are deeply jealous of clerics, chanters, rogues, druids, wizards etc<br>
<br>
I do engage in class balances discussions. I do offer positive suggestions. I make big long posts and do huge analyse dps vs downtime or SCM3 vs MC1 vs SCF3. I tackle stereotypes, both positive and negative. I get annoyed when people slag off a class - any class. But I never let it get to my enjoyment of the game. When I'm in the game I am totally absorbed by it, by my character; I HATE class balance discussions in /guildsay or on my guild boards, I normally switch it off. When I'm in game I do what I can do and dont worry about what anyone else can do, and if my abilities get nerfed I get no more angry at SoE than I'd get angry at God if someone I knew died. When I do get burnt out in game, which happens, I do something else in game or I take a break.<br>
<br>
I dont expect any game to ever be anywhere near perfect - no game prior to EQ over the last 20 years ever was and EQ is no different. But EQ has kept me captivated for 100x longer than any previous game and for that I am truly grateful. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=santerai>santerai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 137<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/13/03 5:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards of Norrath UNITE!</span><hr size=1> I love my wizard just fine, thank you. There are some issues that could use some tweaking, but all and all, a wizard is a kick ass class. If you're not having fun, then play another class. Most of the time if you're unhappy, you're not doing something right. Maybe you don't like to be a caster, or maybe you just plain suck at a wizard.<br>
<br>
The whole LFG thing .. you know, I went through this alot too, but so do other classes. I have done 98% of my exp in grps, so I have alot of friends outside my guild, I know people, people remember me. I am also very active on my server message board, so that also helps me when I am LFG. If I LFG too long, I'll start to make a grp with whoever is shouting, and now and days the LFG tool.<br>
<br>
and Draughts &gt; all.  <br>
